INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4125,5,'2010-10-15 12:39:50','2010-10-15 16:39:50','<strong>Programmer from Zhongshan, China Wins 2010 TopCoder Open Software Development Competition </strong>\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\n\n<strong>Las Vegas, Nev., October 15, 2010</strong>  TopCoder, Inc., the leader in online programming competition, skills assessment and competitive software development platforms, today announced that Yang Li of Zhongshan, China, is the Development Competition Champion of the 2010 TopCoder Open, the worlds foremost competitive computer programming and creative design tournament.\n\nLi, known by his TopCoder Community handle <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/tc?module=MemberProfile&amp;cr=15604762\">Yeung</a>, was one of nine Chinese finalists in the competition who were joined by competitors form Ukraine, Philippines, Sri Lanka, Romania and Nigeria.\n\nThe competition challenged the competitors to develop solutions across multiple technology platforms and development languages. Li won with over 14,000 total points and programmed primarily in .NET.\n\nHe was also a finalist in the TopCoder Open Mod Dash competition.\n\nI was fortunate in this competition and my project work helped a lot. I am very happy to have earned a $20,000 prize, said Li. I think I will put this prize towards buying a house or car.\n\n<strong><em> </em></strong>\n\nThe event took place October 11<sup>th</sup> -14<sup>th</sup> at the MGM Mirage in Las Vegas as 82 top performers from around the world competed across multiple tracks for a share of $150,000 in prizes. More details are available at <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/tco10\">http://www.topcoder.com/tco10</a>. The 2010 TopCoder Open was supported in part by sponsors <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/tc?module=Static&amp;d1=tournaments&amp;d2=tco10&amp;d3=overview&amp;d4=sponsor1\">Yandex</a>, <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/tc?module=Static&amp;d1=tournaments&amp;d2=tco10&amp;d3=over