INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (4163,5,'2010-10-08 13:05:50','2010-10-08 13:05:50','<h1>TopCoder shares in $14.2M defense pact</h1>\nGlastonbury software developer TopCoder Inc. is sharing in a $14.2 million defense contract to devise an online regimen meant to boost flagging interest among the nation\'s youth in math, technology, engineering and science.\n\nThe three-year contract is from the Defense Advanced Research Projects Agency (DARPA).\n\nTopCoder will collect $5.6 million under the contract in collaboration with the University of Arizona. It is TopCoder\'s first federal contract, a spokesman says.\n\nThe university\'s \"Teach Ourselves\" initiative will create a distributed, online community of middle- and high-school students and teachers.\n\nTopCoder\'s assignment is to create the online platform to introduce students to math and the other topics. The site will rely on collaborative activities, such as puzzles and problem-solving games, webisodes, workshops, and other content, to draw students to the site daily, officials say.\n\nStudents also will use it to track their advancement through various subjects, qualifying for points they can redeem for real goods.\n\nDARPA officials said in a statement that raising the pool of mathemeticians, scientists, engineers and others is vital to increasing America\'s computer science innovation necessary for keeping the defense department\'s computer networks secure - both vital to national security.\n\nPrivately held TopCoder relies on a virtual network of computer programmers to develop software for customers.','TopCoder shares in $14.2M defense pact','','publish','closed','open','','topcoder-shares-in-14-2m-defense-pact','','','2010-10-08 13:05:50','2010-10-08 13:05:50','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=4163',0,'post','',0);
