INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5418,5,'2011-02-25 16:05:21','2011-02-25 16:05:21','The TopCoder competition spec review process has been integrated in <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/direct\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a>. As a user setting up the contest, you no longer need to leave Cockpit to complete the spec review. You can simply view the spec review progress when looking at the contest, see the reviewers comments, reply with your own comments and resubmit the contest inputs for review.\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/02/spec_review_1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5419\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/02/spec_review_1-300x154.png\" alt=\"spec_review_1\" width=\"300\" height=\"154\" /></a>\n\nPlease report any issues or feature requests to <a href=\"mailto:support@topcoder.com\">support@topcoder.com</a>.','Spec Reviews in Cockpit','','publish','closed','open','','spec-reviews-in-cockpit','','','2011-02-25 16:05:21','2011-02-25 16:05:21','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5418',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5463,5,'2011-03-15 15:55:18','2011-03-15 19:55:18','An initial release of the <a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/help/template-help/\" target=\"_blank\">TopCoder Help Center</a> is live.  There is some initial content loaded and more coming quickly.  The content is primarily being created via TopCoder\'s new <a href=\"http://apps.topcoder.com/wiki/display/tc/Content+Contests+Overview\" target=\"_blank\">Content Creation</a> contests.  As much as possible, we\'d like the topics for the content to come from users.   So, please tell us what you\'d like to see in the Help Center.  Have a question or topic you want to hear more about?  Ask <a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/help/template-help/\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/03/Help-Center_1300137629543.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5467\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/03/Help-Center_1300137629543-300x204.png\" alt=\"Help Center\" width=\"300\" height=\"204\" /></a>','Help Center','','publish','closed','open','','help-center','','','2011-03-15 15:55:18','2011-03-15 19:55:18','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5463',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5492,5,'2011-04-14 13:19:19','2011-04-14 17:19:19','Issue tracking has been added to <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/direct\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a>. When viewing a contest you can now see all <a href=\"http://apps.topcoder.com/wiki/x/WYTD\" target=\"_blank\">Bug Races</a> that are tied to that contest as well as any other general tickets that are related to the contest.\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/04/cockpit_issue_tracking_1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5494\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/04/cockpit_issue_tracking_1-300x151.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"151\" /></a>The next version will include a view of issues tracked against an entire project as well as stats and health indicators added to the dashboard views.','Issue Tracking Added to Cockpit','','publish','closed','open','','issue-tracking-added-to-cockpit','','','2011-04-14 13:19:19','2011-04-14 17:19:19','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5492',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5673,5,'2011-06-17 11:05:02','2011-06-17 15:05:02','If you haven\'t been in Cockpit in a few weeks, take a peek. Our community has been busy making UI and general usability improvements. Some are already in and more are on the way. A few things you may notice...\n<ul>\n	<li>Improved table layouts and columns included</li>\n	<li>New header, footer and sidebar. Need help? Check out the help widget in the sidebar.</li>\n	<li>Check your calendar. A first version of a calendar view of your contests is live. A more robust calendar/gantt/list view is in the works.</li>\n</ul>\nThe next few weeks will unveil a new and improved contest dashboard and a much improved metrics dashboard. Here are some previews...\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/06/chart_prev_1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5674\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/06/chart_prev_1-300x101.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"101\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/06/chart_prev_2.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5675\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/06/chart_prev_2-300x102.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"102\" /></a>\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/06/contest_dashboard_prev1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5676\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/06/contest_dashboard_prev1-300x105.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"105\" /></a>\n\nEnjoy!','Cockpit UI Improvements','','publish','closed','open','','cockpit-ui-improvements','','','2011-06-17 11:05:02','2011-06-17 15:05:02','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5673',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5694,5,'2011-06-23 15:13:19','2011-06-23 19:13:19','Did you know that <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direcet\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a> can help you provision and distribute environments on virtual machines (VM\'s) to TopCoder members participating in competitions? As a user of the platform, you can request access to manage VM\'s in Cockpit. The Cockpit VM Manager allows you to configure an EC2 account, add AMI\'s and then grant permission to specific users to be able to create and destroy VM\'s on demand. You can then track active VM\'s across all of your projects and competitions in one centralized place. Better yet, let your copilots manage this process for you to really increase the amount of work you can get done.\n<p style=\"text-align: center\"><a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/help/files/2011/04/VM-Management.gif\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"../help/files/2011/04/VM-Management-300x180.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"180\" /></a></p>\nVM\'s are being used for many things in the TopCoder Platform, but generally they are used to enable the power of the community. Here are a few examples of how customers are using the Cockpit VM Manager:\n<ul>\n	<li><em>Development </em>- The community can have the required development environment distributed to them on their own VM. This eliminates environment setup time and lets the competitor focus on the important tasks of the competition. It also helps maintain consistency and reduces integration issues since everyone is working from a mirror of the same environment.</li>\n	<li><em>Testing </em>- Setup an application/website/etc. on a VM where the community can test it for you via Testing Competitions and/or Bug Hunts. Also, be able to test/validate submissions from competitors in real time. Part of the submission requirements are live apps on the competitors\' VM\'s.</li>\n	<li><em>Version Control/Merge Management</em> - Enable the community to manage the merging and versioning of source code as it gets delivered from competitions. This can remove a lot of bottlenecks if you have an active development force, bring you to market quicker.</li>\n	<li><em>Proof of Concepts</em> - Engage the community to build and deploy proof of concepts, application ideas, experimental architectures, etc. directly onto VM\'s were you can see them and let your customers see them without the need to manage your own environments.</li>\n</ul>','VM Management','','publish','closed','open','','vm-management','','','2011-06-23 15:13:19','2011-06-23 19:13:19','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5694',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5710,5,'2011-07-15 10:30:22','2011-07-15 10:30:22','The TopCoder Community is continuing to make great improvements to <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct/\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a>. Among the latest are improvements to the Contest Dashboard and Project Dashboard, which were driven by customer demand.  Here is a quick peek at what the new features look like...\n\n<strong>Contest Dashboard:</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/07/dashboard_contest_1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5712\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/07/dashboard_contest_1-300x162.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"162\" /></a>\n\n<strong>Project Dashboard:</strong>\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/07/dashboard_project_1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5713\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/07/dashboard_project_1-300x249.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"249\" /></a>\n\nYou will see many additions coming, especially to the project dashboard. Next week, look out for some nice additions to the enterprise dashboard view....','Contest and Project Dashboard Updates','','publish','closed','open','','contest-and-project-dashboard-updates','','','2011-07-15 10:30:22','2011-07-15 10:30:22','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5710',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5725,5,'2011-08-12 16:36:26','2011-08-12 16:36:26','Metrics, metrics, and more metrics.  The enterprise dashboard view has been updated with additional metrics.  Among other things, you can use them to understand how your projects and contests are performing compared to other contests/projects and the market as a whole.  Here are some questions that the data is answering for me:\n<ul>\n	<li>- What is my average cost per contest?  What is the range of cost?</li>\n	<li>- How many contests have I run over the past 6 months?  What is my monthly average?</li>\n	<li>- What is my average duration for producing results?  What is the range?</li>\n	<li>- What is my success rate when running contests?</li>\n	<li>- What % of the market (in terms of volume) do I represent?</li>\n</ul>\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/08/dashboard_metrics1.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5730\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/08/dashboard_metrics1-300x132.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"132\" /></a>\n\nIt\'s nice to have this data, but it\'s also nice to be able to act on it. For example, I noticed earlier in the year that my fulfillment % was lower than the market average and it was trending downward. This was having a negative impact on my expected timelines and outcomes. I then noticed my contest duration was longer than average and my costs were also higher. I wanted to increase my fulfillment, since that gives me more predictability in my timelines. In order to do so, my copilots took the lead and decomposed my projects into smaller parts (contests). That resulted in a lower cost and duration per contest and my fulfillment increased from 75% to 95%, giving me an increased ability to deliver product on time and on budget.','New Dashboard Metrics','','publish','closed','open','','new-dashboard-metrics','','','2011-08-12 16:36:26','2011-08-12 16:36:26','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5725',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (5737,5,'2011-08-12 16:52:24','2011-08-12 16:52:24','Many users of <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct/\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a> are now managing projects for multiple customers. In such a scenario, it has become difficult to keep track of which contests apply to which customer when looking at your actively running contests and projects. To help you keep organized and focused, we\'ve added a simple dropdown to the sidebar that allows you to select a specific customer you\'re working with or \"All Customers\". This will filter your active view to include only contests and projects that pertain to the selected customer.\n\n<a href=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/08/sidebar-customer.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-5738\" src=\"http://topcoder.com/home/files/2011/08/sidebar-customer-188x300.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"188\" height=\"300\" /></a>','Multiple Customer Filtering','','publish','closed','open','','multiple-customer-filtering','','','2013-12-03 23:28:09','2013-12-04 04:28:09','',0,'http://topcoder.com/home/?p=5737',0,'post','',0);
