INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (6984,5,'2011-05-14 09:31:08','2011-05-14 09:31:08','<h2><span style=\"font-size: 13px;font-weight: normal\">TopCoder is based on innovation. We have created the first ever competitive software development methodology. We need your help to manage and evolve our process of competitive innovation and software development. We are looking for smart, passionate people that are quick learners and can successfully onboard the TopCoder process at enterprise customers.</span></h2>\n<strong>Responsibilities:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Work closely with customers to explore and identify business and software needs  educate customers on using tactical and strategic innovation within their organization.</li>\n	<li>Guide customers in the use of an innovative, distributed software development methodology in order to add significant value to their business.</li>\n	<li>Manage project timelines, budget, and distributed process controls.</li>\n	<li>Help to improve TopCoders innovative, competitive software development methodology and associated processes.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Other Requirements:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Bachelor degree.</li>\n	<li>Must be willing to travel Monday-Friday within the continental United States.</li>\n	<li>Candidates must be US Citizens, have a valid Green Card, or be eligible for a TN visa.</li>\n</ul>\nTopCoder is passionate about innovation and building long lasting relationships with companies interested in finding a better way to do things. To start or continue a management career in a forward-thinking environment that offers a lucrative compensation structure focused on performance,<a href=\"mailto:jobs@topcoder.com?subject=Platform%20Manager\">apply for this job</a>\n\n&nbsp;','TopCoder Platform Manager','','trash','open','open','','topcoder-platform-manager','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',8068,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=6984',0,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (6986,5,'2011-05-14 09:31:37','2011-05-14 09:31:37','Competition is the driving force behind TopCoder. What started as simply trying to identify the worlds best technical talent became a re-engineering of the entire software development process.<strong>We are now looking to build the best sales team in the business</strong>  a team that is passionate about innovations in technology, building relationships with customers, and with the desire to be a part of a thriving, entrepreneurial and rapidly growing company. Our sales team plays a critical role in defining, creating and executing a strategy to penetrate the worlds leading companies to provide technology solutions to drive their businesses.<a href=\"http://software.topcoder.com/applications/index.jsp\">Learn more</a>\n\n<strong>Candidates MUST be able to:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Fit into the TopCoder culture: integrity, strong work ethic, forward-thinking and a successful mindset for themselves, our organization and our clients.</li>\n	<li>Deeply understand the superiority of our business model and be motivated by the opportunity to have a role in changing how software is developed today.</li>\n	<li>Immediately begin development of a sales pipeline and creation of a business plan including specific target accounts and strategies to exceed revenue goals.</li>\n	<li>Balance aggressively identifying potential revenue-generating prospects with developing long-lasting, relationship-based business partnerships that benefit both parties.</li>\n	<li>Visualize and articulate innovative ways TopCoder can have a direct, beneficial impact on a prospects business.</li>\n	<li>Think outside of the cold-call the CIO box.</li>\n	<li>Utilize strong research and networking skills critical for pipeline/account development.</li>\n	<li>Demonstrate interest in exploring the latest technology trends and gadgets.</li>\n	<li>Utilize social networking tools like LinkedIn/Facebook/blogs/forums etc.</li>\n	<li>Travel frequently. This position can be based anywhere in the US.</li>\n</ul>\n<strong>Qualifications:</strong>\n<ul>\n	<li>Bachelors degree.</li>\n	<li>Demonstrated strong selling skills or an aptitude for identifying/closing business opportunities.</li>\n	<li>A basic understanding of software development  although the ability to discuss social networking, crowdsourcing and other Web 2.0 concepts would suffice.</li>\n	<li>Candidates must be US Citizens, have a valid Greencard, or be eligible for a TN visa.</li>\n</ul>\nTopCoder is passionate about innovation and building long lasting relationships with companies interested in finding a better way to do things. To start or continue a sales career in a forward-thinking environment that offers a lucrative compensation structure focused on performance including a corporate benefits package,<a href=\"mailto:jobs@topcoder.com?subject=Salesperson\">apply for this job</a><a>.</a>\n\n&nbsp;','Business Development Specialist','','trash','open','open','','business-development-specialist','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',8068,'http://localhost/wordpress/?page_id=6986',0,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7007,5,'2011-05-12 17:22:59','2011-05-12 17:22:59','<h2>Website and Digital Content</h2>\nYour website is the primary location for your company to share your story, your impact and what sets your company apart from the competition. Customers and prospects  consumers or businesses  use your website as a first and frequent source of information about what your company does, what you sell, and how they can buy.Effective communication is asolid foundation for your website, however you\'ll need to go a lot further if you are looking to build an audience or convert visitors to buyers.\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Going beyond static content by creating interactive and engaging media.</li>\n	<li>Integrating your website with social media channels, like YouTube, Twitter and Facebook.</li>\n	<li>Measuring how changes to your website impact user behavior.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Elite creative talent generates multiple approaches for your media challenges.</li>\n	<li>Results focused engineering to iteratively build and refine your website using the right technologies.</li>\n	<li>Analytic capability to understand your users and how your content impacts their behavior.</li>\n</ul>','Website and Digital Content','','trash','closed','closed','','website-digital-content','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',7762,'http://www.topcoder.com/',1,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7013,5,'2011-05-12 17:27:17','2011-05-12 17:27:17','<h2>Business Applications</h2>\n<p>You want to provide your customers the best service and experience possible, and that means using software to help your employees be their best. Business applications cover a wide range of functions, from process automation, to business intelligence, to scheduling - these are very real opportunities to make your customers happy.</p>\n\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</strong></h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Should you buy (COTS), build (custom development), or rent (Software-as-a-Service)?</li>\n	<li>Upgrading existing systems to support customer demands for modern capabilities.</li>\n	<li>Building the right team and staffing elite talent to ensure the projects complete on time and on budget.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Engineering process focused on business results regardless of platform.</li>\n	<li>Built in scale to let your priorities drive what gets done, not your internal capabilities.</li>\n	<li>Drastically reduce project management and administrative over head while engaging the world\'s best talent.</li>\n</ul>','Business Applications','','trash','closed','closed','','business-applications','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',7762,'http://www.topcoder.com/',2,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7015,5,'2011-05-12 17:28:08','2011-05-12 17:28:08','<h2>Mobile, Tablet, &amp; Television</h2>\n<p>Your customers are spending more and more of their time on mobile and tablet devices instead of on a PC. At the same time traditional TV is evolving into an application based experience. Your success is driven by meeting your users and consumers at the screen of their choice.</p>\n\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Capturing new and rapidly evolving market places for mobile and other devices.</li>\n	<li>Supporting the varying technical and functional capabilities across platforms.</li>\n	<li>Ensuring quality standards are met without holding up release schedules.</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>A variety of competitions and challenges exist that let you seek out new ideas for taking your core capabilities into new markets.</li>\n	<li>The TopCoder community has many early adopters who excel at rapidly digesting new API\'s and program languages, so you don\'t have to worry about the \"how\".&lt;/\n	<li>Quality control is integrated with each competition and quality assurance is a standard part of the process, so you\'ll know your applications meet your standards.</li>\n</ul>','Mobile, Tablet, and Television','','trash','closed','closed','','mobile-tablet-television','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',7762,'http://www.topcoder.com/',3,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7018,5,'2011-05-12 17:29:07','2011-05-12 17:29:07','<h2>Open Platforms &amp; APIs</h2>\n<p>Your customers demand open platforms and APIs so they can customize and further integrate your products. If you can successfully provide this openness, then your customers will become co-creators: building more functionality upon your core platform. Customers who co-creators are less likely to leave and more likely to evangelize your products and that can mean more customers and happier customers.</p>\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>How can you retro-fit existing systems to support an open platform model?</li>\n	<li>Have you provided enough developer resources (SDKs, documentation, examples) to ensure a quick ramp up?</li>\n	<li>How do you field test your API to make sure it\'s ready for release?</li>\n</ul>\n<br />\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Competitions can reverse engineer existing systems and design approach for upgrading where needed to support opening of APIs.</li>\n	<li>Our community is the target demographic for your API and will collaborate with you on identifying and fixing any problems.</li>\n	<li>Parrellel scale allows you to build example applications to validate the API directly, without sacrificing other development.</li>\n</ul>','Open Platforms and APIs','','trash','closed','closed','','open-platforms-apis','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',7762,'http://www.topcoder.com/',4,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7022,5,'2011-05-17 16:26:11','2011-05-17 16:26:11','<h2>Community Building </h2>\n<p>The act of creating an open platform and API does not guaranteeconsumer participation, co-creation or growth. Itreadies you for thatpath, butthe key ingredient is still absent, your community. Building an impassioned and eager to innovate community can take much longer than anticipated and at a far greater cost.</p>\n\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Seeding and growing a new community with the right people.</li>\n	<li>Developing a platform to collaborate and engage community members.</li>\n	<li>Aligning the community with your goals and objectives.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>An active community ready to go on day one, without the costs of building your own.</li>\n	<li>Ever expanding community collaboration tools for real engagement.</li>\n	<li>Incentives - learning, recognition, payment - align community with your business.</li>\n</ul>','Online Community Building','','trash','closed','closed','','online-community-building','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',7760,'http://www.topcoder.com/',8,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7026,5,'2011-05-17 16:27:53','2011-05-17 16:27:53','<h2>Idea Generation</h2>\n<p>Innovation is critical to your company, and idea generation is critical to innovation. In the digital arena, you have an opportunity to re-think traditional services, capture new customers, and disrupt existing markets. It all starts with a diversity of new ideas.</p>\n\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>How do you reach beyond your core constituencies (employees and customers) to bring real diversity to your innovation pipeline?</li>\n	<li>Will resource competition with current projects and operations leave ideas to spoil on the vine?</li>\n	<li>Can you validate your ideas in a global marketplace?</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>A global community of innovators and a cutting edge idea generation capability.</li>\n	<li>Platform for developing ideas into prototypes, beta versions, and production releases that scales on demand.</li>\n	<li>Ability to continuously refine new ideas through iteration and measure their impact down stream.</li>\n</ul>','Idea Generation','','trash','closed','closed','','idea-generation','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',7760,'http://www.topcoder.com/',5,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7028,5,'2011-05-17 16:28:20','2011-05-17 16:28:20','<h2>Prototype Challenges</h2>\n\n<p>Developing ideas in your innovation pipeline requires making choices: Which ideas will you fund? Which will be discarded? How far along development will you take an idea before you make these choices? When you are resource constrained, you have take a chance by trying to pick the right idea up front. The problem is you don\'t have enough information to be right, it takes lots of chances to find success.</p>\n\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Picking and choosing between candidate ideas to decide which ones to prototype.</li>\n	<li>Making go - no go decisions before you\'ve experienced an idea and field tested it.</li>\n	<li>Transitioning products from prototype to full production.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Make better decisions about ideas by prototyping many in parallel.</li>\n	<li>Validate ideas with your customers using functioning code and not just power points.</li>\n	<li>High quality deliverables ensured by peer review, allow for rapid transition to product development.</li>\n</ul>','Prototype Challenges','','trash','closed','closed','','prototype-challenges','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',7760,'http://www.topcoder.com/',6,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7030,5,'2011-05-17 16:29:08','2011-05-17 16:29:08','<h2>Product Concepts</h2>\n<p>Sometimes you have an idea that requires due diligence and the development of requirements before you can get investment. Typically that means compiling market or business requirements, which often get stuck at 80% done, cost more than they should, and are discarded soon after. You need a way to meet this demand effectively and efficiently.</p>\n\n<h3>Challenges You\'ll Face</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Will your staff constantly be pulled in different directions keeping documentation from getting finalized?</li>\n	<li>Are you moving into an area where developing expertise is cost prohibitive?</li>\n	<li>Can you marshal a wide range of disciplines when their involvement is only sporadic?</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>The TopCoder Difference</h3>\n<ul>\n	<li>Competitions have integrated review ensuring they drive high-quality, 100% done outcomes.</li>\n	<li>Our global community\'s wide range of expertise rapidly responds to your challenges.</li>\n	<li>Multiple disciplines form dynamically assembled virtual teams, simplifying your management efforts.</li>\n</ul>\n</span>','Software Product Concepts','','trash','closed','closed','','software-product-concepts','','','2013-12-10 22:06:22','2013-12-11 03:06:22','',7760,'http://www.topcoder.com/',7,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7750,5,'2011-06-14 19:49:24','2011-06-14 19:49:24','Running software projects and innovation challenges can be hard work. TopCoder copilots make it easier.\n\nWhen you start a new project the first thing you\'ll do is request a copilot. The copilot will be an experienced community member, skilled at taking your requirements and translating them into a series of competitions. This let\'s you keep your focus where it needs to be: on your business.\n\nSee the community\'s <a class=\"big\" href=\"http://apps.topcoder.com/wiki/display/tc/Copilot+Overview\">copilot information page</a> for more details.\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_7849\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\" caption=\"A TopCoder Copilot makes your job easier\"]<img class=\"size-medium wp-image-7849 \" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2011/07/copilot.jpg\" alt=\"A TopCoder Copilot makes your job easier\" width=\"480\" height=\"422\" />[/caption] ','Copilots','','trash','open','open','','copilots','','','2013-12-10 22:06:22','2013-12-11 03:06:22','',12840,'http://www.topcoder.com/',1,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7760,5,'2011-06-14 20:20:29','2011-06-14 20:20:29','Innovation is the driver of gaining and maintaining market share for companies. If your firm is relying on software products or any other digital assets as part of the products and processes that will drive your future growth, you need to innovate in those areas. At the same time it is difficult for companies to predict which ideas and technologies will drive future innovation. Is your company falling behind it\'s competitors in the innovation game?\n<ul>\n	<li>Can your employees generate the necessary diversity of ideas entering your innovation funnel?</li>\n	<li>Does your company have the resources to develop and test ideas so they\'ll have a more chances at finding commercial success?</li>\n	<li>Can you quickly pivot from a prototype and discover mode into full product development lifecycle when needed?</li>\n	<li>How will you build a broader community of stakeholders beyond the traditional employee and customer base?</li>\n</ul>\nTopCoder\'s digital innovation program can deliver solutions to these challenges to make you competitive in the innovation playing field.\n\nFind out more about our innovation solutions\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"./idea-generation/\">Idea Generation</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"./prototype-challenges/\">Prototype Challenges</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"./software-product-concepts/\">Software Product Concepts</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"./online-community-building/\">Online Community Building</a></li>\n</ul>','Digital Innovation','','trash','open','closed','','digital-innovation','','','2013-12-10 22:06:22','2013-12-11 03:06:22','',12839,'http://www.topcoder.com/',1,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7762,5,'2011-06-14 22:15:04','2011-06-14 22:15:04','If your company has software  products then you face  the challenge of  increasing your development capacity to meet demand, while  also facing  pressure to become efficient. HR processes  and management layers are  hold overs from  the industrial revolution  that are not suited to meet  the challenges of  the information age.\n<ul>\n	<li>As your company has grown, has it been more and more difficult to add great talent to your team?</li>\n	<li>As your products mature, are engineers less interested in working on them?</li>\n	<li>Have you ever wondered why you know what you want, and have engineering staff, but can never get them together?</li>\n	<li>Are recognition and rewards driven by something other than business results?</li>\n</ul>\nTopCoder\'s product development programs provide unlimited development   capacity, transparent processes and integrated quality, in an outcomes   model. This means you can focus on what you want to build, instead of   how to manage employees. It\'s a new paradigm for the information age.\n\nFind out about projects that a Product Development program can support\n<ul>\n	<li><a href=\"./website-digital-content/\">Websites and Digital Content</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"./mobile-tablet-television/\">Mobile, Tablet, and Television</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"./business-applications/\">Business Application</a></li>\n	<li><a href=\"./open-platforms-apis/\">Open Platforms and APIs</a></li>\n</ul>','Product Development','','trash','closed','closed','','product-development','','','2013-12-10 22:06:22','2013-12-11 03:06:22','',12839,'http://www.topcoder.com/',2,'page','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7905,5,'2011-05-03 03:52:19','2011-05-03 03:52:19','<em>World\'s Largest Competitive Development Community to Offer $5,000 in Cash Prizes for Milestone Member Appreciation Event\n</em><strong>\n<strong>GLASTONBURY, Conn., March 3, 2011</strong></strong> -- TopCoder, Inc., today announced that it will hold its 500th Single Round Match (SRM) on Saturday, March 19th, 2011. To commemorate this milestone achievement, the match will offer $5,000 in cash prizes in appreciation of the dedication and passion for algorithmic competition as exemplified by the TopCoder Community. SRM 500 begins at 12:00 noon EDST (GMT-4).  Cash prizes totaling $5,000.00 will be distributed amongst top performing rated members in both the Division I and Division II competition groups. For full details visit: <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/tc?module=MatchDetails&amp;rd=14429\">http://www.topcoder.com/tc?module=MatchDetails&amp;rd=14429</a>\n\nTopCoder is a community of talented people passionate about software programming  students, professionals, computer scientists, mathematicians, physicists, doctors and representatives from all fields and disciplines collaborate, learn, work and compete in the world\'s foremost professional and collegial innovation ecosystem.\n\nTopCoder Single Round Match Stats\n\n	The first ever SRM on May, 8th, 2001 attracted 81 competitors.\n	Current matches attract 1,800 participants biweekly (~20X increase).\n	Over the past decade more than 43,000 unique competitors have entered the TopCoder Arena to test their skills and talents against the best algorithmists in the world.\n	In 2008 alone, over 44,000 unique individuals from around the globe spent more than 770,000 hours in the TopCoder arena competing and/or practicing in the extensive practice rooms.\n	TopCoder Community currently lists over 280,000 total members, more than 40,000 of whom are rated with in excess of 7,000 active within the last six months\n	Ten years worth of problem sets are available in the TopCoder Arena practice rooms  and registration is free. For full details on how to compete visit http://www.topcoder.com/wiki/display/tc/How+to+Compete+in+Algorithm+Competitions\n\n\"It has been rewarding to see the TopCoder arena grow from a small competition portal into a well respected social hub and powerful educational tool, where thousands of problems are freely available for practice with tens of thousands of solutions for review and dissection,\" said Mike Lydon, CTO of TopCoder. \"The International nature of SRMs is fun to witness - seeing thousands of intelligent people from all corners of the world congregate during each event is an amazing experience.\"\n\n<strong>About TopCoder Single Round Matches</strong>\n\nThe Algorithm competitions are timed contests where all contestants compete online and are given the same problems to solve under the same time constraints. The competitions are available in four programming languages: Java, C#, C++, and VB.NET. Each Single Round Match (SRM) consists of three phases: Coding Phase (75 min), Challenge Phase (15 min), and System Testing Phase.\nThe Coding Phase is a timed event where all contestants are presented with the same three questions representing three levels of complexity and, accordingly, three levels of point earnings potential. Points for a problem are awarded upon submission of any solution that successfully compiles and are calculated on the total time elapsed from the time the problem was opened until the time it was submitted.\n\nThe Challenge Phase is a timed event wherein each competitor has a chance to challenge the functionality of other competitors\' code. A successful challenge will result in a loss of the original problem submission points by the defendant, and a 50-point reward for the challenger. Unsuccessful challengers will incur a point reduction of 25 points as a penalty, applied against their total score in that round of competition.\n\nThe System Testing Phase is applied to all submitted code that has not already been successfully challenged. If the TopCoder System Test finds code that is flawed, the author of that code submission will lose all of the points that were originally earned for that code submission. The automated tester will apply a set of inputs, expecting the output from the code submission to be correct. If the output from a coder\'s submission does not match the expected output, the submission is considered flawed. The same set of input/output test cases will be applied to all code submissions for a given problem. All successful challenges from the Challenge Phase will be added to the sets of inputs for the System Testing Phase.\n\n<strong>About TopCoder, Inc.</strong>\nTopCoder is the world\'s largest competitive software development community and platform with more than 280,000 developers representing over 200 countries. TopCoder hosts the largest and most comprehensive developer ratings and performance metrics available. The TopCoder community builds software and community platforms for a wide-ranging client base through a competitive, rigorous, standards based methodology. For more information about sponsoring TopCoder events and utilizing TopCoder\'s software services and platforms, visit <a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com\">www.topcoder.com</a>.','TopCoder Single Round Match #500 Announced for March 19th','','publish','open','open','','topcoder-single-round-match-500-announced-for-march-19th','','','2011-05-03 03:52:19','2011-05-03 03:52:19','',0,'http://www.topcoder.com/?p=7905',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (7918,5,'2011-06-17 04:15:36','2011-06-17 04:15:36','<p><a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/clip_image002.gif\" mce_href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/clip_image002.gif\"><img src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/clip_image002.gif\" mce_src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/06/clip_image002.gif\" alt=\"\" class=\"alignnone size-thumbnail wp-image-5624\" height=\"150\" width=\"150\"></a><br mce_bogus=\"1\"></p>\n<p>Announcing the AMD OpenCL coding competition! Heres your chance to get hands-on experience withheterogeneous computing and the award-winning AMD Fusion accelerated processing unit (APU) architecture.<br />\nWell be judging the submission here at TopCoder in the following OpenCL application development categories (as well as others!):</p>\n<p><b>Video &amp; Image Processing</b></p><p><b>\n<p>Security</p>\n<p>Human Computer Interface</p>\n<p>Data Mining</p>\n<p>Gaming</p>\n<p>Physics processing</p>\n<p>Social Networking</p>\n<p>Communication</p>\n</b></p><p><b>Other </b></p>\n<p>Developers and students who choose to participate will be asked to submit an abstract that outlines how they plan to use the latest generation AMD APP software development kit (SDK) with OpenCL support to create an accelerated application for the AMD Fusion APU platforms.</p>\n<p>For full details and a complete set of Official Rules, visit <a href=\"http://community.topcoder.com/amdapp/\" mce_href=\"http://community.topcoder.com/amdapp/\">http://community.topcoder.com/amdapp/</a> </p>\n<p>The OpenCL Coding Competition is open to all software developers with great ideas. And the one of the best parts? Up to $50,000 in prizes will be awarded to winning submissions!</p>','AMD Launches the OPENCL Coding Competition!','','publish','open','open','','amd-launches-the-opencl-coding-competition','','','2011-06-17 04:15:36','2011-06-17 04:15:36','',0,'http://www.topcoder.com/?p=7918',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8065,5,'2011-05-02 04:15:18','2011-05-02 04:15:18','This is an example page. It\'s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I\'m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin\' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickies to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href=\"http://localhost/coba/cobabug/wordpresshomequick/wp-admin/\">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!','Sample Page','','trash','open','closed','','sample-page','','','2013-12-10 22:05:16','2013-12-11 03:05:16','',0,'http://localhost/coba/cobabug/wordpresshomequick/?page_id=2',0,'page','',0);
