INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8363,5,'2011-09-30 19:42:38','2011-09-30 19:42:38','<br/>\n<img class=\"alignleft\" style=\"float: left;\" title=\"Copilot_Step1\" src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Copilot_Step1-300x162.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"162\" />\n\n<a href=\"http://community.topcoder.com/tc?module=ViewCopilotPool&amp;size=20&amp;view=0&amp;sort=12\" target=\"_blank\">Copilots</a> play a major role in the TopCoder Platform. They help you plan, provide estimates, runcontests, manage projects and most importantlyhelp you get the results you need. In keeping with the spirit of things, some of our copilots have been working to improve our copilot process. Our latest release changes the flow that a customer uses to <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct/copilot/launchCopilotContest\" target=\"_blank\">engage a copilot</a>. The engagement process is used by customers to discuss a potential \"project\" with the copilots, get some cost/time estimates, strategize on the approach, and then start working with a copilot(or several copilots) to run the project.\n\n<br/><br/><br/><br/>\n\n\n\n<a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/ProjectOverview_1.png\"><img class=\"alignright\" style=\"border-style: initial; border-color: initial; float: right;\" title=\"ProjectOverview_1\" src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/ProjectOverview_1-300x88.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"88\" /></a>\n\nTo make it easier to communicate with your copilots and have a discussion around the project, the Project Overview page has also been updated. You\'ll now find a quick view of your copilots, a way to add/remove copilots from the project, and a project level discussion thread that is accessible to your copilots as well as anyone you grant project access to.\n\nGive it a try and let us know what you think. As always, send feedback to <a href=\"mailto:support@topcoder.com\">support@topcoder.com</a>.','Working with a copilot just got a little easier...','','publish','open','open','','working-with-a-copilot-just-got-a-little-easier','','','2013-12-03 23:28:09','2013-12-04 04:28:09','',0,'http://www.topcoder.com/?p=8363',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8409,5,'2011-10-05 13:50:08','2011-10-05 13:50:08','Now you can see an aggregate view of how many community members are participating in your projects. The first version of the <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct/dashboardParticipationReport\" target=\"_blank\">Participation Metrics</a> report has been released in <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a>. You can find in under the <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct/dashboardParticipationReport\" target=\"_blank\">Reports</a> tab. Your data will give you a sense of how much leverage you are getting by using the TopCoder Platform. For example, I now can see the following view for projects that I\'ve been running over the past 6 months:\n\n<a href=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Cockpit_Participation_Metrics.png\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-medium wp-image-8410\" title=\"Cockpit_Participation_Metrics\" src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Cockpit_Participation_Metrics-300x214.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"214\" /></a>\n\nYou might also notice a nice improvement to the look and feel of the filters on all the reports.','Who is participating in my projects?','','publish','open','open','','who-is-participating-in-my-projects','','','2013-12-03 23:28:09','2013-12-04 04:28:09','',0,'http://www.topcoder.com/?p=8409',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8510,5,'2011-10-20 15:25:44','2011-10-20 15:25:44','You can now filter your billing report in Cockpit by specific contest IDs. This was added in response to users asking for an easy way to see all of the data for a specific contest. Enter the contest ID and only the cost elements of that specific contest will be returned.\n\n<img src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Cockpit-Billing-ContestID-Filter.png\" alt=\"Billing Cost Report Image\" width=\"954\" height=\"1022\" />','See Costs by Contest','','publish','open','open','','filter-billing-by-contest','','','2013-12-03 23:28:09','2013-12-04 04:28:09','',0,'http://www.topcoder.com/?p=8510',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8516,5,'2011-10-20 15:34:47','2011-10-20 15:34:47','A nice little feature was added to <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a> last night.  When a software competition (ex: an Architecture Competition) is progressing through Final Fixes and Approval, the user often wants the most recent version of the submission that is in progress. When viewing the Submissions page in <a href=\"https://www.topcoder.com/direct\" target=\"_blank\">Cockpit</a>, you\'ll now notice an area that tracks Final Fixes and allows the user to download the most up-to-date version of the asset.\n\n<img src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Cockpit-Submissions-Software.png\" alt=\"Software Submission Viewer\" width=\"955\" height=\"560\" />','Track and Download Final Fixes and Final Versions','','publish','open','open','','track-and-download-final-fixes-and-final-versions','','','2013-12-03 23:28:08','2013-12-04 04:28:08','',0,'http://www.topcoder.com/?p=8516',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8520,5,'2011-10-20 15:51:22','2011-10-20 15:51:22','<img style=\"float: right;\" src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Cockpit-Start-Project-Icon.png\" alt=\"Start Project Button Image\" width=\"231\" height=\"30\" />The first version of the new user experience to start your projects in Cockpit is now live. You\'ll notice a pretty big change. A few things to note:\n<ol>\n	<li>Context sensitive instructions are included on each step in the process to help guide the user.</li>\n	<li>You can see some sample game plans as you setup your project. Soon, this will morph into the ability to browse sample projects, see costs/timelines, and automatically load the game plan into your Cockpit when you save the project. Stay tuned next month for this release.</li>\n	<li>Either select a copilot you have agreed to work with on the project, or setup a new posting to talk to all the copilots about your project.</li>\n	<li>Assign additional resources to your project. This can be any TC member - your team members, a TC PM, etc.</li>\n	<li>A nicer confirmation page that guides you onto the next steps.</li>\n</ol>\n<img src=\"http://www.topcoder.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/10/Cockpit-Start-Project-1.png\" alt=\"Start Project Game Plan Template Image\" width=\"800\" height=\"439\" />','Start Your Project!','','publish','open','open','','start-your-project','','','2013-12-03 23:28:08','2013-12-04 04:28:08','',0,'http://www.topcoder.com/?p=8520',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (8540,5,'2011-10-21 20:03:01','2011-10-21 20:03:01','<span>Brendan has worked for TopCoder since 2005 in a variety of roles. Currently  he leads marketing and strategic initiatives. His responsibilities include lead generation and  development, content and social marketing, and community development. Prior to  his current role he ran the high tech practice for enterprise accounts - helping  high tech companies develop and execute programs to leverage TopCoder\'s  Community and Platform.</span>\n\n<span> </span>\n\n<span>Prior to joining TopCoder Brendan spent three years at FlightView as Chief  Engineer where he oversaw all technical operations and product development.He  started his career as a software consultantworking on a variety of eCommerce  and enterprise data warehouse projects. Brendan received his BA in Computer Science from Boston College.\n</span>','Brendan Wright','','trash','open','open','','brendan-wright','','','2013-12-10 22:06:22','2013-12-11 03:06:22','',12842,'http://www.topcoder.com/',7,'page','',0);
