INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12550,5,'2012-07-28 01:41:53','2012-07-28 01:41:53','In June 2001, Robert Hughes was named President and Chief Operating Officer of TopCoder, Inc. of Glastonbury, Connecticut. He is responsible for overseeing the day-to-day operations of the company. Prior to his role at TopCoder, Hughes served as the Chief Operating Officer of Talln Inc. since 1997. Talln is an Internet professional services firm that creates fully-integrated, technologically advanced solutions for their clients.\n\nDuring his tenure with Talln, the company was recognized as one of the fastest-growing technology companies in North America four years in a row by consultancy firm Deloitte &amp; Touche and by Inc. magazine for its outstanding performance. In 2000, CMGI, Inc. acquired a majority ownership of the company.','Robert Hughes','','publish','open','closed','','robert-hughes','','','2012-07-28 01:41:53','2012-07-28 01:41:53','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12437',0,'leadership','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12551,5,'2012-07-28 02:13:20','2012-07-28 02:13:20','Joining TopCoder Software in 2002 as Vice President of Software Development, Michael P. Morris brings more than a decade of technology experience across vertical markets with diverse clients including AOL, Disney, ESPN, PayPal and VeriSign among others. His proven expertise in disciplines such as Component Based Development and Mobile Web services have earned him industry recognition and conference speaking engagements.\n\nFormerly, Morris was director of design and development for Talln, where he successfully managed projects for companies such as Barnes &amp; Noble, eBay, Bertlesmann and Loudeye. He was previously a project manager and consultant with Talln as well. Prior to Talln, Morris served as software programmer for Invensys, a developer of process automation and resource tracking software. He received his BA in Computer Science from Boston College.','Michael Morris','','publish','open','open','','michael-morris','','','2012-07-28 02:13:20','2012-07-28 02:13:20','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12442',0,'leadership','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12552,5,'2012-07-28 02:14:30','2012-07-28 02:14:30','David Tanacea joined TopCoder as president in 2002, bringing more than 20 years of experience to TopCoder Software. As General Manager of TopCoder\'s Enterprise Platforms division, he oversees the technology direction and distribution of TopCoder Software\'s application development offerings for Fortune 500 companies.\n\nPrior to joining TopCoder Software, Tanacea spent seven years with Talln and as general manager leading development efforts for marquee Fortune 1000 companies, including Priceline, Ingram Micro, PepBoys, Mott\'s, Bloomingdale\'s, Talbots and Best Buy. Tanacea was previously vice president of information technology for Zany Brainy, vice president of development for Ann Taylor and director of merchandising systems for WaldenBooks. Tanacea launched his career in the early 1980\'s with Eastman Kodak as an application developer.','David Tanacea','','publish','open','open','','david-tanacea','','','2012-07-28 02:14:30','2012-07-28 02:14:30','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12446',0,'leadership','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12553,5,'2012-07-28 02:16:05','2012-07-28 02:16:05','Ira Heffan has been working with TopCoder since 2001, previously as outside counsel to the company, and now as its General Counsel. Heffan brings to TopCoder over ten years of experience in working with technology companies on their legal matters, particularly in the areas of intellectual property and community-based models. Prior to joining TopCoder, he was in the Intellectual Property Transactions and Strategies Group of the law firm Goodwin Procter. Heffan holds a JD from Stanford Law School, an MS in Computer Science from Boston University, and a BSEE from Union College.','Ira Heffan','','publish','open','open','','ira-heffan','','','2012-07-28 02:16:05','2012-07-28 02:16:05','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12450',0,'leadership','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12554,5,'2012-07-28 02:19:05','2012-07-28 02:19:05','Mike Lydon joined TopCoder in April of 2001 as the Chief Technology Officer. Lydon brought to TopCoder his 10 years of experience designing and managing large-scale distributed web-based and data-warehousing systems. Prior to joining TopCoder, Lydon worked as Vice President of Technology Services at Talln. Lydon holds a business degree from the University of Connecticut where his focus was on Information Systems.','Mike Lydon','','publish','open','open','','mike-lydon','','','2012-07-28 02:19:05','2012-07-28 02:19:05','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12453',0,'leadership','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12555,5,'2012-07-28 02:20:11','2012-07-28 02:20:11','Brendan has worked for TopCoder since 2005 in a variety of roles. Currently he leads marketing and strategic initiatives. His responsibilities include lead generation and development, content and social marketing, and community development. Prior to his current role he ran the high tech practice for enterprise accounts - helping high tech companies develop and execute programs to leverage TopCoder\'s Community and Platform.\n\nPrior to joining TopCoder Brendan spent three years at FlightView as Chief Engineer where he oversaw all technical operations and product development.He started his career as a software consultantworking on a variety of eCommerce and enterprise data warehouse projects. Brendan received his BA in Computer Science from Boston College.','Brendan Wright','','publish','open','open','','brendan-wright','','','2012-07-28 02:20:11','2012-07-28 02:20:11','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12456',0,'leadership','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12556,5,'2012-07-28 02:21:52','2012-07-28 02:21:52','Jim McKeown joined TopCoder in 2004 as director of communications and is responsible for TopCoder\'s global communication, marketing and brand management strategy and execution. He brings more than a decade of experience in the field of strategic communications and public relations to TopCoder and manages the company\'s integrated marketing, public relations, media and analyst relations. Prior to joining TopCoder, McKeown held account positions with Boston high tech public relations firms Schwartz Communications and Copithorne &amp; Bellows.\n\nMcKeown holds a Master\'s Degree in Public Relations from Suffolk University, Boston.','Jim McKeown','','publish','open','open','','jim-mckeown','','','2012-07-28 02:21:52','2012-07-28 02:21:52','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12461',0,'leadership','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (12557,5,'2012-07-28 02:22:28','2012-07-28 02:22:28','Tony Jefts joined TopCoder in 2005 and brings almost 15 years of experience in leadership and delivery of cutting edge technology solutions to high profile corporations. At TopCoder, as Director of Product Development, he spearheads the product and process development efforts that directly support TopCoders unique and innovative platform model. By leveraging TopCoders own platform and global community, Tony has transformed the way TopCoder accomplishes all of its technology and creative needs, and placed that same capability in the hands of its customers. He is one of the inventors on three separate patents, all focused on various aspects of creating platforms and processes to support scaling global innovation platforms and putting them in the hands of real end users.\n\nBefore joining TopCoder, Jefts held the position of Project Manager at Talln where he managed the delivery of high-end enterprise systems for many Fortune 100 companies. During his 4+ year tenure with Talln, he delivered a wide range of value to his customers in such areas as online news content syndication, data warehousing and business intelligence, distribution and warehouse management and optimization, and mobile development.\n\nTony earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Computer Science from Binghamton Universitys Watson School of Engineering.','Tony Jefts','','publish','open','open','','tony-jefts','','','2012-07-28 02:22:28','2012-07-28 02:22:28','',0,'http://localhost/wordpress/secondary/?post_type=leadership&amp;p=12465',0,'leadership','',0);
