INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (13112,3,'2013-12-05 23:41:45','2013-12-05 23:41:45','<h3>Related Test Crowdsourced Development</h3>\n<p>CloudSpokes is the leader in crowdsourced cloud development work. Founded in 2011 by <a href=\"http://www.appirio.com\">Appirio</a>, CloudSpokes has quickly become the largest community of cloud development experts in the world. For businesses, the flexibility of cloud platforms has created a unique situation where, for the first time, anyone with an Internet connection and the right skill can be an enterprise development partner. For the CloudSpokes community, this approach creates a market for their talents, lets them develop new skills with real world assignments and transition their careers to the cloud, learn from the work of others, and establish their credibility as skilled practitioner in the art and science of cloud development.</p>\n\n<h3>A Cloud of Technical Talent</h3>\n<p>Cloud platforms have changed the way technology is delivered. We no longer need to run our own datacenters to access the computing power we require. We can pay for the compute resources we need, when we need them, and access the best resources regardless of where we are. But when it comes to development talent, we still rely on in-house teams and on site consultants. What if there was an easy way to tap into the creativity of the smartest cloud developers, as needed? CloudSpokes matches companies who need cloud development expertise with a worldwide community of more than 70,000 specialist developers that enterprises can call upon as needed. CloudSpokes incorporates a community competition and peer-review model that reduces development costs and drives innovation by ensuring the best solutions rise to the top.</p>\n\n<h3>Community-driven Innovation</h3>\n<p class=\"halfPb\">The CloudSpokes model focuses on results, and competing to find the best solution. The community brings a unique expert perspective to a development, design, or architecture challenge:</p>\n<ul>\n                                    	<li><strong class=\"listTitle\">Extend a core system</strong> <span class=\"listTitleDash\">-</span> New additions, and app extensions are great opportunities for innovation. CloudSpokes allows core-teams to focus on their specialty, while bringing in thousands of experts as needed, when needed, for expertise beyond the four walls of an organization.</li>\n                                    	<li><strong class=\"listTitle\">Creative challenges</strong> <span class=\"listTitleDash\">-</span> Certain problems, by their very nature, can be solved in a number of ways, but its the creativity of that solution that will separate success from failure. Choosing from multiple approaches ensures the best fit is chosen at the start.</li>\n                                    	<li><strong class=\"listTitle\">Loosely-coupled apps</strong> <span class=\"listTitleDash\">-</span> By breaking down a large application into its individual elements, CloudSpokes can drive agile innovation on each individual element, all at the same time. Faster, better, and at a fraction of the cost of other approaches. Welcome to truly agile development.</li>\n                                    </ul>\n<h3>Real Results</h3>\n<p class=\"halfPb\">CloudSpokes works with leading enterprises and ISVs in search of talent and development resources:</p>\n<div class=\"csRealResults grid group\">\n                                        <div class=\"grid-3-1\">\n  											<section class=\"realResult\">\n                                            	<img src=\"http://localhost/1.Create/TCS/lt/wp/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/logo-box.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"111\" height=\"41\" class=\"csLogo\">\n                                                <p><strong>Hosting Boxs first-ever Mobile Developer Hackathon using the CloudSpokes platform was simply the beginning. Box has since run multiple CloudSpokes challenges including an Evernote plugin, an iPad application, and a PHP Library for their API.</strong></p>\n												<p>\"We\'re excited to be working with CloudSpokes - we believe that their contest platform and community of developers will be immensely helpful in spurring innovation in the cloud.\" </p>\n                                                <p class=\"quoterName\">Alex Willen</p>\n                                                <p class=\"quoteTitle halfPb\">Platform Marketing at Box</p>\n                                            </section>\n                                        </div>\n                                        <div class=\"grid-3-1 gird-rt\">\n                                        	<section class=\"realResult\">\n                                                <img src=\"http://localhost/1.Create/TCS/lt/wp/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/logo-jdrf.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"143\" height=\"41\" class=\"csLogo\">\n                                                <p>\"We needed to have a single place to collect data on all of the people that support us. We need to make sure all of our donor records are centralized into a single repository in our Salesforce app. We\'re finally at a point with the cloud technologieswith the way they\'re all designedwhere we can have fully integrated systems and still have a single record per customer. Nothing upsets people who support nonprofits more than seeing us waste money on sending them multiple mailings or emails. Having a single record per constituent is critical. CloudSpokes provided a way for JDRF to create the support application quickly and at a lower cost.\"</p>\n                                                <p class=\"quoterName\">James Szmak</p>\n                                                <p class=\"quoteTitle\">CIO at JDRF</p>\n                                            </section>\n                                        </div>\n                                    </div>','Overview related','','publish','open','open','','overview-related','','','2013-12-