INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (13178,10,'2013-12-12 16:17:25','2013-12-12 21:17:25','<p><h2>WHITEPAPERS, EBOOKS, VIDEO<br />AND MORE</h2></p>\n<p>Research and content on the future of open innovation.</p>\n\n<h3>SAUGATUCK WHITEPAPER</strong></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/sponsors/resources/saugatuck\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/document.png\"></a></p>\n<p>Explore independent research from Saugatuck Research on Enterprise Crowdsourcing with CloudSpokes.</p>\n\n<h3>WEBINAR: COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT</h3>\n<p><a href=\"/sponsors/resources/saugatuck\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/webinar_saugatuck.png\"></a></p>\n<p>Mike West of Saugatuck, and Mike Morris, GM of CloudSpokes, discuss the benefits of a community software development model.</p>\n\n<h3>Webinar: Crowdsourced Development LifecycleWEBINAR: CROWDSOURCED DE</h3>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y_lB1qGDM0o\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/cloudspokes_utest_webinar.png\"></a></p>\n<p>A pioneering webinar with uTest to show the new power of community development and testing.</p>','Resources','','inherit','closed','closed','','102-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-12 16:17:25','2013-12-12 21:17:25','',102,'http://beta.topcoder.com/102-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (13179,10,'2013-12-12 16:25:02','2013-12-12 21:25:02','<p><h2>ENTERPRISE COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT</h2></p>\n<p>Explore independent research from Saugatuck on the benefits of crowdsourcing in enterprise IT:</p>\n\n<p><h3>WHITEPAPER</h3></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><a href=\"http://go.appirio.com/saugatuckwhitepaperdownload\"><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/document.png\" /></a><br /><a href=\"http://go.appirio.com/saugatuckwhitepaperdownload\">DOWNLOAD</a>\n</p>\n\n<p>Cloud technology has made it easy to scale apps and infrastructure, but scaling cloud resources is still a bottleneck to growth and innovation.  Addressing this mismatch will be the difference between firms that use technology and those that differentiate themselves through it.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://www.saugatucktechnology.com\">Saugatuck Technology</a>, an analyst firm focusing on how emerging technologies drive real change in business, recently published a report on why and how crowdsourcing is making an impact on enterprise IT and product R&amp;D.</p>\n\n<h3>WHAT IS CROWDSOURCING &amp; COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT?</strong>\n<ul><li>How can enterprises use external communities of developers to greatly amplify access to technical talent and skills that are perfectly matched to each development task? How does this augment current in-house and outsourced teams?</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>WHAT ARE THE LESSONS LEARNED FROM OTHER ENTERPRISES?</strong>\n<ul><li>Hear direct quotes from industry peers that have tapped into a community development model to drive innovation.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<strong>WHAT ARE THE ADVANTAGES OF A COMMUNITY DEVELOPMENT MODEL?</strong>\n<ul><li>Tapping into thousands of the world\'s best cloud experts, with a model that\'s 62% more effective, is just the beginning.</li>\n</ul>','Saugatuck','','inherit','closed','closed','','107-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-12 16:25:02','2013-12-12 21:25:02','',107,'http://beta.topcoder.com/107-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (13180,10,'2013-12-13 15:14:23','2013-12-13 20:14:23','<h2>EFFICIENT ACCESS TO THE WORLD\'S BEST TECHNICAL TALENT</h2>\n\n<h3>CLOUD RESOURCES</h3>\n\n<p>Cloud platforms have changed the way technology is delivered. We no longer need to run our own datacenters to access the computing power we require. We can pay for the compute resources we need, when we need them, and access the best resources regardless of where we are. But when it comes to technical talent, we still rely on in-house teams and on site consultants.</p>\n\n<p><strong>What if there was an efficient way to tap into the creativity of the smartest people in the world, as needed?</strong></p> \n\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img style=\"padding:10px\" src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/top_talent.png\" width=\"250px\"/></p>\n<p>TopCoder matches companies who need technical expertise with a worldwide community of more than 600,000 experts. TopCoder incorporates a community competition and peer-review model that reduces development costs and drives innovation by ensuring that the best solutions rise to the top.</p>\n\n<h3>GET STARTED</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>POST YOUR CHALLENGE - TopCoder flips the model for getting development work done. Instead of focusing on the resource and hours required to complete a project, TopCoder allows you to focus on the outcomes you want from the beginning. Post your challenge, and watch the community of experts compete to provide the best solution. You can dictate the number of submissions, the complexity of the submissions, and even the specific languages used.</li>\n\n<li>FACILITATE THE DISCUSSION - From confirmation around which technologies and languages are acceptable, to clarity on the posted requirements, discussions drive value. The discussion area at the bottom of each challenge can help flush out details which may not have ever been clear in the first place (validation on the end product before it\'s even created). The community members want to ensure that they\'re successful, so these discussion questions are completely focused on driving value for the end result.</li>\n\n<li>SCORE THE SUBMISSIONS - Scorecards are provided up-front for each challenge so the community members have a clear understanding of how their solution will be graded. Upon completion, the challenge judges will have a list of submissions and the associated scorecards under their individual profile. To ease the review process, all TopCoder challenges require a video, demo, or preview of the submitted asset - often this overview is all that is required to confirm the winning solutions.</li>\n\n<li>RETRIEVE YOUR ASSETS - IP Ownership of a TopCoder challenge submission is always transferred to the challenge sponsor (whoever pays for the challenge, owns the final products that were paid for). After the review process is complete, all the submitted assets are available right on a private challenge page for the challenge sponsor to retrieve and install wherever appropriate.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/breezi_placeit.png\" width=\"100%\" /></p>\n<h3>FAQ</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>QUALITY - Only submissions that meet the requirements are accepted. For front-end design and innovation challenges, it\'s a subjective decision that chooses the winners. For development challenges, a rigorous, pre-defined scorecard determines the best solution. For algorithm and analytics challenges, the top submissions are judged on performance.</li>\n\n<li>SECURITY - TopCoder uses a 3rd party service  Checkmarx, to provide <a href=\"/customers/how-it-works/thurgood/\">static code analysis</a> to ensure asset security. Each asset receives thorough scanning for comprehensive vulnerability, via intelligent, repeatable, risk exploration queries.</li>\n\n<li>IP - The <a href=\"/customers/how-it-works/privacy-policy/\">Terms of Service</a> state clearly that the sponsor will retain ownership and IP of any materials created. IP and materials generated through a TopCoder challenge are always transferred to the challenge sponsor.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>REAL RESULTS</h3>\n<p>TopCoder works with leading enterprises, ISVs, and government agencies in search of talent and development resources:\n</p>\n\n<h3>READ OUR <a href=\"/customers/what-we-do/case-studies\">CASE STUDIES >></a><br />AND OUR <a href=\"/community/stories\">COMMUNITY STORIES >></a></h3>','How It Works','','inherit','closed','closed','','30-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-13 15:14:23','2013-12-13 20:14:23','',30,'http://beta.topcoder.com/30-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
